--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q1. Signed char minimum value: -128

Explanation:
A char occupies 8 bits(1byte) of memory.One of the 8 bits of the memory is used to store either + or -.As it is signed char it occupies    from [-128 to 127).The minimum value of signed char is -128.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q2. Signed char maximum value: 127

Explanation:
A char occupies 8 bits of memory which is equivalent to 1 byte.One of the 8 bits occupy either + or -.It takes the values from [0 to 128).The maximum value that it can take is 127.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q3. Unsigned char minimum value: 0

Explanation:
A char occupies 8 bits of memory which is equivalent to 1 byte.As it is an unsigned char it takes values from [0 to 256) of which it takes all positive values only.The minimum value that it takes in unsigned char  is 0.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q4.  Unsigned char maximum value: 255

Explanation:
A char occupies 8 bits of memory which is equivalent to 1 byte.As it is an unsigned char it takes values from [0 to 256) of which it takes all positive values only.The maximum value that it takes in unsigned char is 255.      
